DK21 does not include javax.xml.bind. Should I include test dependencies? For the isXmlField Class.forName with the javax.xml.bind annotation, I might need the jaxb-api. Hibernate could also be added, but the rule states that tests should be outside library packages. If I create a helper package for org.hibernate in tests, it may complicate things. I wonder if adding hibernate-core is too heavy, or if I should create a test source instead. It's tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test file structure**\\n\\nThis suggests having only one test file for each class, but what about helper classes? It says to maintain coverage in dedicated Java test files. Maybe I could use nested classes in TypeUtilsTest, but org.hibernate can’t be nested, so perhaps I should skip the Hibernate site. I also need to ensure I maximize coverage without running the tests. I should check the current coverage. For the TypeUtilsTest.java, I think public placeholders can stay, but I need to be cautious with reflection in tests, only using it when necessary for public APIs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring GenericArrayType for primitives**\\n\\nI’ve uncovered a need for a GenericArrayType when dealing with primitive arrays. I’m wondering if I can get the Type by using a field like int[][] for this generic array. It seems like GenericArrayType would occur for T[] types, but not for primitives. If the field type is GenericArrayType with a primitive Class, does that mean I need a custom implementation? I’m also questioning if using a custom GenericArrayType in tests without reflection would be considered direct access. That’s a bit confusing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_v7usnBFoNAScYJS6ZsuiDYaz|fc_000de0be998528f4016a0193e8b318819ebaa557ec34d03a4f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"removeMixIn\\|addMixIn\" -n /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.alibaba/fast